The Master of Science in Physics is a two-year Master's programme taught in English. 

The University of Amsterdam (UvA) is internationally renowned for its physics research activities.  Other institutes, such as the Dutch National Institute for Subatomic Physics (Nikhef), in which the UvA collaborates, are also situated here.

